`TextareaAutosize` is not a drop-in `inputComponent`: `OutlinedInput` passes it an `inputRef` prop, which `TextareaAutosize` forwards to its native `<textarea>`, triggering the React warning.

Use the built-in multiline support instead:

```jsx
<OutlinedInput
  multiline
  rows={3}        // fixed height
  // or:
  // rows={undefined}
  // minRows={3}
  // maxRows={8}
  {...otherProps}
/>
```

`OutlinedInput` renders and wires up `TextareaAutosize` itself when `multiline` is enabled. If you must provide a custom `inputComponent`, wrap it and consume/handle `inputRef`; MUI documents that as part of the custom-component contract. [MUI v4 text field docs](https://v4.mui.com/components/text-fields/)
